essentially She's an an amputee with dreams of marrying a human. An artist drew her on /trash/ a while back.
>Now her dreams of marrying a human are looking slim. About 8lbs slim. At least she's still got her piano... Oh wait.

>She goes to her favorite hole-in-the-wall while she still has time off from work. She rarely treats herself to steak, but she needs some cheering up. Her friend seems to be late but she orders anyway. People are chatting. With no co-diner to focus on, she frequently notices the sideways glances the she gets. Over time her smile (if she had one) drops. She's still sitting alone as the entree finally arrives. As she thanks her waiter she begins to warm up a little happy once more, until she realizes she can't cut it one-handed without making a mess.
Her mouth twitches downward as she fights to suppress her frown. She knows she's going to break down. She feels like splitting right that moment.
She mutters it a couple times, but then she gets it out. "Waiter." An older employee, a fox, turns.
"Yes," he says, instantly noticing her stub a full half of a second before making eye contact. He looms over her. "What is it?" She's silently crying.
"Could I," she says, gasping a bit, whimpering a bit, feeling a droplet crash onto her chest, sting in her eyes. Sting in her eyes. "Could I have this sliced up?" She waits ugly, looking at his default scowl. Though she momentarily has someone to talk to, she notices the mean looks she's getting even more. She tries to breathe. Then she notices her friend paused at the entrance. The crying becomes much harder to keep quiet.
The steak didn't end up hitting the spot.
